The paper deals with saliency detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and the proposal of a new saliency metric based on the AUC property suggest that the paper also falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of datasets and the evaluation of saliency systems suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
